  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubSciFi000001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A single-shot polymer thread, injected at the base of the skull, that overlays raw sense-data from compromised neural archives onto the user's perception. Slicers use it to read systems like books; the comedown is paranoid and fragmentary.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 10 minutes you have advantage on Intelligence (Investigation) checks made to discern hidden patterns, encoded data, or surveillance feeds.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Memorywire (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Memorywire.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Charisma checks (you tend to narrate other people's intentions before they do).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 3.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(3 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Syringe.</em></p>"
    },
